In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June 15, 2013, as World Elder Abuse Awareness Day. He acknowledges that elder abuse is a global public health problem that affects people from all backgrounds and cultures. The Obama Administration is committed to preventing elder abuse through various initiatives, such as the Elder Justice Act. They are working to identify risk factors for abuse and neglect, empower seniors to meet financial challenges, and pursue a criminal justice response to hold offenders accountable. The president calls upon all Americans to learn the signs of elder abuse, neglect, and exploitation and raise awareness about this issue.